SIMPLE: improve
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Improve
<hw>Im*prove"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>prove</ets>: cf. L. <ets>improbare</ets>, F.
<ets>improuver</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To disprove or make void;
to refute.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Neither can any of them make so strong a reason which another can
not <qex>improve</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Tyndale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To disapprove; to find fault with; to reprove; to
censure; <as>as, to <ex>improve</ex> negligence</as>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When he rehearsed his preachings and his doing unto the high
apostles, they could <qex>improve</qex> nothing.</q>
<rj><qau>Tyndale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Improve</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Improve
<hw>Im*prove"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Improved</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Improving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>in-</ets> in +
<ets>prove</ets>, in <ets>approve.</ets> See <er>Approve</er>,
<er>Prove.</er>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make better; to increase the
value or good qualities of; to ameliorate by care or cultivation;
<as>as, to <ex>improve</ex> land</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Donne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I love not to <qex>improve</qex> the honor of the living by
impairing that of the dead.</q> <rj><qau>Denham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To use or employ to good purpose; to make
productive; to turn to profitable account; to utilize; <as>as, to
<ex>improve</ex> one's time; to <ex>improve</ex> his means.</as></def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We shall especially honor God by <qex>improving</qex> diligently
the talents which God hath committed to us.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A hint that I do not remember to have seen opened and
<qex>improved</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The court seldom fails to <qex>improve</qex> the opportunity.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How doth the little busy bee⟦br⟧
<qex>Improve</qex> each shining hour.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those moments were diligently <qex>improved</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Gibbon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>True policy, as well as good faith, in my opinion, binds us to
<qex>improve</qex> the occasion.</q> <rj><qau>Washington.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To advance or increase by use; to augment or add to;
-- said with reference to what is bad.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We all have, I fear, . . . not a little <qex>improved</qex> the
wretched inheritance of our ancestors.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Porteus.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To better; meliorate; ameliorate; advance;
heighten; mend; correct; rectify; amend; reform.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Improve</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Improve
<hw>Im*prove"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To grow better; to
advance or make progress in what is desirable; to make or show
improvement; <as>as, to <ex>improve</ex> in health</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We take care to <qex>improve</qex> in our frugality and
diligence.</q> <rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To advance or progress in bad qualities; to grow
worse.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Domitian <xex>improved</xex> in cruelty.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milner.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To increase; to be enhanced; to rise in value;
<as>as, the price of cotton <ex>improves</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>To improve on</b></col> <it>or</it> <col><b>To
improve upon</b></col></mcol>, <cd>to make useful additions or
amendments to, or changes in; to bring nearer to perfection; <as>as,
<ex>to improve on</ex> the mode of tillage</as>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>improved</ent>⟦br⟧
